==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.}} {{term|trigonometria|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|τρίγωνον||triangle|sc=polytonic|tr=trigōnon|lang=grc}} + {{term|-metria||-metry|lang=la}}.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|trigonometries|-}}

# {{mathematics}} The branch of [[mathematics]] that deals with the [[relationship]]s between the [[side]]s and the [[angle]]s of [[triangle]]s and the [[calculation]]s based on them, particularly the [[trigonometric function]]s.

